"title": "5278: cripples",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5278",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>People whose walk, physical or spiritual, is hindered by deformity, permanent or temporary.</p>\n<h2>Physically crippled from birth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:2\">ACT 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:8\">ACT 14:8</a></p>\n<h2>Physically crippled in life</h2>\n<h3>By accident</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:4\">2SA 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:3\">2SA 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:13\">2SA 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>By God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:24-Gen32:25\">GEN 32:24–32:25</a></strong> <em>God had a purpose in the crippling of Jacob: it was a mark of his meeting with God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:31-Gen32:32\">GEN 32:31–32:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:21\">HEB 11:21</a></p>\n<h3>By Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11\">LUK 13:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:16\">LUK 13:16</a></p>\n<h2>Cripples healed</h2>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:4-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:4–11:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:30-Matt15:31\">MAT 15:30–15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:1-John5:9\">JHN 5:1–5:9</a></p>\n<h3>By others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:7\">ACT 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:9-Acts4:10\">ACT 4:9–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:7\">ACT 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:9-Acts14:10\">ACT 14:9–14:10</a></p>\n<h2>Cripples and OT sacrifice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:18-Lev21:19\">LEV 21:18–21:19</a></strong> <em>A man must be without defect.  Physical disability is a defilement to holiness.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:6\">LEV 21:6</a></p>\n<h3>Crippled animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:8\">MAL 1:8</a></strong> <em>Animals, like people, must be holy, without defect, when brought to the LORD.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:5\">EXO 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1\">LEV 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:3\">LEV 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:18-Lev22:25\">LEV 22:18–22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:14\">NUM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:3\">NUM 28:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:21\">DEU 15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:1\">DEU 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:13-Mal1:14\">MAL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual aspects of being crippled</h2>\n<h3>Physical crippling preferable to spiritual lameness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8\">MAT 18:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:29-Mark5:30\">MRK 5:29–5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:43\">MRK 9:43</a></p>\n<h3>Cripples disadvantaged in life but welcome in the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:6-Mic4:7\">MIC 4:6–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:8\">JER 31:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:16\">EZK 34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:13\">LUK 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:21\">LUK 14:21</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual cripples healed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:6\">ISA 35:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:13\">HEB 12:13</a></p>",
